      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Generally, if the damage is isolated to a small area - missing shingles, a single leak point, damaged flashing around one penetration - a repair is the most cost-effective solution. If your roof is over 15-20 years old, has widespread damage, multiple leak points, or significant decking deterioration, a full replacement is usually the better long-term investment. Happy Roof provides honest assessments. We will never recommend a replacement when a repair will do the job.</div>
